	<li class="comment byuser comment-author-rudyneeser comment-author-is-site-member even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 highlander-comment" id="comment-431" >
		<div class="c-grav"><img alt='' src='https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/12e39f7c4cfdc4a96d2e64988b07a8c5?s=40&#038;d=identicon&#038;r=G' class='avatar avatar-40' height='40' width='40' /></div>
		<div class="c-body">
			<div class="c-head">
				<a href='http://rudyneeser.wordpress.com/' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Rudy Neeser</a> <span class="c-permalink"><a href="https://micfic.wordpress.com/2010/08/22/flight-792/#comment-431">permalink</a></span>
			</div>
						<p>Our Hero, the traditionally named Agent Smith, reports at a crash site where he then proceeds to replace the plane&#8217;s black-box with another. He is about to cover up that birds caused the crash of flight 792.</p>
<p>I enjoyed the officious, agent-type banter between the characters. One gets the sense that Agent Smith is more competent — and higher up in the food chain — than poor Agent Jones. Good use of language for this (such as having Jones &#8220;scamper&#8221; off). </p>
<p>I thought that they sometimes overused calling each other agent. For instance, &#8220;Anytime today, Agent,&#8221; sounded a bit forced to me.</p>
<p>At the end I was left wondering how Agent Smith was going to remove the bodies of the birds from the plane to finish the cover up, but also thought that this was a good beginning for him!</p>
<p>Fun piece <span class='wp-smiley wp-emoji wp-emoji-smile' title=':)'>:)</span></p>
						<div class="reply">
				<a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='https://micfic.wordpress.com/2010/08/22/flight-792/?replytocom=431#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm( "comment-431", "431", "respond", "222" )' aria-label='Reply to Rudy Neeser'>Reply</a>			</div>
